PS: is that how DoT stacking works? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yanbun>Yanbun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 573<br> <font color=#333333>(11/12/02 10:48:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: .</span><hr size=1> No need to flame here. Yes, we argue with each other, but it should never get hostile.<br>
<br>
<br>
Only classes (very situational, and needing the right 61+ rare spells) that I know of that can solo at 64+ are:<br>
<br>
Rangers - Bow kiting forever (literally 10 minutes per kill)<br>
Bards - Bard kiting forever (longer than rangers)<br>
Mages - Frenzy Kiting for a long time, (3-4 minutes per kill) Or Chaincasting for awhile.<br>
Necros/Druids - Root/Dot, takes awhile but low mana<br>
Enchanters (probably the only class who can do it well) - Charm soloing (and no, not with DC)<br>
SK - Very rarely can solo where fear and snare stick<br>
Beastlord - Takes forever and a lot of mana, but doable<br>
Paladin - Root/Heal takes awhile, takes forever against non-undead<br>
Wizards - Seen very few wizards do well with a Snare-Root-Rain-Stun combo, but takes a lot of mana and hard to pull off. Regular Snare-Root-Nuke also can work, but takes a lot of mana and can be risky.<br>
Shamans - Can kill mobs, but takes as long as rangers.<br>
<br>
Now, of these, only Necros, Druids, and Enchanters can solo for any reasonable amount of experience. Enchanters are best at it, but their soloing is very risky. Death happens a lot. Necros and Druids have a less risky way to do it, but experience comes slow, even though mana usage is low. <br>
<br>
Mages probably come after these classes, when Chaincasting or Frenzy kiting. The Nuke/Heal method may sometimes be viable when using the Earth pet. <p>&quot;History is just a set of lies agreed upon&quot; - Emperor Napoleon Bonaparte<br>
